<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-349-525  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 349 525.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  Jan 5 1989 n1145 p56(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DTI drops fibre optics despite comms upheaval. (Department ofTrade and Industry)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Moran, Nuala.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Department of Trade and Industry has decided to let marketforces be the deciding factor in the creation of a fiber opticcommunications grid.andP;  The decision is based upon a study done bythe PA Consulting Group in 1987, which looked at scenarios of agovernment funded fiber optic grid, a lightly regulated regime,and a laissez-faire regime.andP;  PA concluded that BT Telecom willeventually install a fiber optic grid.andP;  The study failed to takeinto account changes in the telecomm industry likely to take placein 1990, including the licensing of rival carriers and thestraight resale of capacity on private networks.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Fiber OpticsTelecommunicationsLegal Issues.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>